70
00:06:37,410 --> 00:06:40,509
The blue ice runway is where the Ilyushin
lands and takes off

71
00:06:40,509 --> 00:06:44,180
it's a hundred meters wide 3,000 meters
long

72
00:06:44,180 --> 00:06:47,620
and the whole of Union glacier camp
exist because of this runway.

73
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:52,340
It's a rare section of ice that
doesn't accumulate new layers of snow each year

74
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:55,640
and as a result can take
and craft with much heavier loads.

75
00:06:55,650 --> 00:07:00,130
the whole stretch a of ice has to be
cleared of snow before the Ilyushin can land

76
00:07:00,150 --> 00:07:03,360
ALE have a large pair of
industrial snow blowers

77
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:09,480
but with strong winds blowing loose snow
down from the mountains almost every day, it's a difficult job

78
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:14,580
The weather in Antarctica can change quickly and dramatically

79
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:19,220
and blizzards can cause white-outs which
smother the campaign in almost zero visibility

80
