and aren't particularly warm at all

95
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:20,180
Most things in camp are within walking distance,

96
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:24,570
but in bad weather it's often easier to
use a Ski-Doo to get around

97
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:36,170
Antarctica may hold the record for the
coldest temperature ever recorded,

98
00:08:36,170 --> 00:08:39,200
but right now it's approaching the
Antarctic summer

99
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:43,890
so the climate is comparatively mild.
Sometimes when the skies are clear

100
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:48,530
and the wind dies down, you can get away
with being outside in just a couple of thin layers

101
00:08:48,590 --> 00:08:52,160
The staff call this a Dingle Day.

102
