In 1959 representatives from a dozen
countries including the US and Russia

389
00:39:44,870 --> 00:39:51,680
met in Washington to sign the Antarctic
Treaty it was an agreement that would make Antarctica free of weapons

390
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:54,730
keeping the continent reserved for
Scientific Research only

391
00:39:54,730 --> 00:39:59,370
All the signatories vow to refrain from
making any claims to territory

392
00:40:00,860 --> 00:40:03,140
today there are fifty states party
to the treaty

393
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:07,460
and in 1998 a protocol on
Environmental Protection came into force

394
00:40:07,460 --> 00:40:12,500
It banned all commercial mining and
designated the whole continent as a nature reserve

395
00:40:12,570 --> 00:40:17,900
Never before or since have nations agreed
to such a comprehensive and firm set of rules

396
00:40:17,990 --> 00:40:21,250
to protect the environment have such a
large part of the world

397
00:40:25,500 --> 00:40:30,040
Since the treaty was signed
investigations have been made into Antarctica's resources

398
00:40:30,310 --> 00:40:34,810
Some suspect it to be the home of the
third largest oil reserve in the world

399
00:40:34,810 --> 00:40:38,330
An estimated $200 billion barrels of oil

400
00:40:38,330 --> 00:40:42,670
This oil is extremely difficult and at
the moment prohibitively expensive to extract

401
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:47,390
but in 2048 when the Antarctic
Treaty is open for review

402
00:40:47,390 --> 00:40:50,680
and when drilling and mining techniques
may be more advanced

403
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:55,000
It is widely considered that the
long-standing ban on this practice will come to an end

404
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:59,930
and much like the warming Arctic north
there is a rush of human activity

405
00:40:59,930 --> 00:41:02,830
to secure these possible reserves

406
00:41:04,310 --> 00:41:07,390
In a world hungry for dwindling fossil
fuels

407
00:41:07,390 --> 00:41:10,480
fresh water scarcity and soaring
energy needs

408
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:14,260
The very countries that signed the
Antarctic Treaty are spending lavishly to

409
00:41:14,260 --> 00:41:15,420
explore the potential

410
00:41:15,420 --> 00:41:18,980
on the world's last unexpoited continent

